1
00:01:35,830 --> 00:01:37,200
Hi.

2
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:39,080
Oh? What brings you here?

3
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:39,990
You didn't even call.

4
00:01:39,990 --> 00:01:41,440
Why do you look so startled?

5
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,320
Were you watching something naughty together?

6
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:44,990
You should've called before coming.

7
00:01:44,990 --> 00:01:46,880
Did you eat dinner?

8
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,240
Probably not.

9
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:49,950
- Go and wash your hands.
- Okay.

10
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:51,510
- Want some snacks?
- Yeah.

11
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:53,420
Snacks? You'll lose your appetite.

12
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:55,650
Eat dinner first.

13
00:02:00,110 --> 00:02:01,680
Did I tell you I became a chairman?

14
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,950
What? Chairman of what?

15
00:02:03,950 --> 00:02:06,800
Some business friends and I started a volunteer organization.

16
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,900
- The chairman of that.
- Whoa...

17
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:12,000
There he goes bragging about useless things.

18
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,630
You asked to meet,

19
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:40,470
but you're not saying anything. Just like old times.

20
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:44,960
Was I like this before, too?

21
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:48,390
Yeah, when we broke up.

22
00:02:52,210 --> 00:02:53,540
Why did you want to see me?

23
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:56,010
The trial's over.

24
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:57,840
Just because...

25
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:02,950
It's been a while since I saw you, An Ju Hyeong,

26
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:06,600
but I don't think I actually got to talk to you.

27
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:09,830
Have you been well?

28
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:11,550
Yeah.

29
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:15,090
I've been doing well, as you can tell.

30
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:20,290
I haven't been well, as you know.

31
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:29,440
I'm sorry... about the trial.

32
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,420
That was the best I could do.

33
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,300
I thought it'd be good to end it quickly.

34
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,680
I know.

35
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:37,360
Ending it fast was the right thing to do.

36
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,590
For my sake as well.

37
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:48,840
After how I had hurt you...

38
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:54,300
I totally deserve this, don't I?

39
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,250
No.

40
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,180
I didn't think that.

41
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:04,790
I did think it would've been better if we hadn't met

42
00:04:04,790 --> 00:04:06,250
under such circumstances.

43
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,460
If we had met under different circumstances,

44
00:04:08,460 --> 00:04:11,530
you wouldn't have even talked to me.

45
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,690
Park Su Jeong,

46
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:21,110
be well.

47
00:04:21,110 --> 00:04:23,590
That's what I came to say.

48
00:04:33,290 --> 00:04:36,970
I used to really like this side of you.

49
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,100
Yeah.

50
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:47,110
I came to say goodbye, too.

51
00:04:48,970 --> 00:04:50,530
Yeah.

52
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,040
Let's not see each other again.

53
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,170
Especially like this.

54
00:04:56,210 --> 00:04:59,620
If something really great happens to you down the line,

55
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:02,140
just send me a text or something.

56
00:05:07,530 --> 00:05:09,930
I'll be fine.

57
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,690
Thanks.

58
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:41,290
Excuse me.

59
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:43,180
An Ju Hyeong left already.

60
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:45,230
You should leave now.

61
00:06:19,650 --> 00:06:21,810
Could you come out for a second?

62
00:06:42,820 --> 00:06:45,260
Well, I asked to see you because—

63
00:06:45,260 --> 00:06:47,630
Let me speak first.

64
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:53,530
I turned Park Su Jeong away.

65
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:56,300
When I went down after what happened yesterday,

66
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:58,140
she was waiting downstairs.

67
00:06:58,140 --> 00:07:01,790
And I ended up telling her you had already left.

68
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:03,110
I crossed the line.

69
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:06,630
I'm sorry. I should've told you right away yesterday.

70
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:12,710
W-Why... did you do that?

71
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:21,520
Yeah, why did I do that...

72
00:07:23,490 --> 00:07:27,100
I guess I didn't want you to get hurt.

73
00:07:33,730 --> 00:07:37,800
I didn't think it'd be good for you to see her in that state.

74
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,930
That's why I did it.

75
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:42,010
You could get hurt needlessly

76
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:44,890
for something that's already in the past...

77
00:07:44,890 --> 00:07:49,370
I mean, maybe not for you, I suppose.

78
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:51,470
So... what I'm trying to say is...

79
00:07:51,470 --> 00:07:53,850
It is in the past.

80
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,290
You were right.

81
00:07:59,290 --> 00:08:02,470
Taking that case was stupid.

82
00:08:02,470 --> 00:08:06,000
I didn't feel at ease with it.

83
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:08,900
But I'm really okay now.

84
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,940
I wanted to tell you that.

85
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:16,500
So... you don't have to feel sorry.

86
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:36,940
I noticed you didn't have any emergency snacks last time,

87
00:08:36,940 --> 00:08:40,360
so I just bought some for you while buying...

88
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,930
buying mine...

89
00:08:46,590 --> 00:08:48,490
Thank you.

90
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:03,820
Please insert your card.

91
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,270
Choose your transaction.

92
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:07,580
Reading your card.

93
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:20,020
Enter the recipient's account number

94
00:09:20,020 --> 00:09:22,820
and press confirm.

95
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:29,290
Enter the amount

96
00:09:29,290 --> 00:09:31,220
and press confirm.

97
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:33,570
Transaction complete.

98
00:09:33,570 --> 00:09:34,900
- What the...
- You scared me!

99
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:37,440
How come you have so much money? You don't spend your salary?

100
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,440
Gosh, why did you sneak a peek at my account?

101
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,820
I'll sue you, I swear.

102
00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:43,330
Sue me? Are we strangers?

103
00:09:43,330 --> 00:09:44,770
- Security!
- Security!

104
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:46,920
- We have a problem here.
- There's no problem.

105
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,890
- We have a problem here, security!
- No problem at all.

106
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,640
This is good.

107
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,230
Let's have lunch here again in two Tuesdays from now.

108
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:05,250
Dip it in the salted shrimp. That's the best.

109
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:06,340
I'll eat it how I want, okay?

110
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:09,520
And who dips chili peppers in salted shrimp?

111
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,610
Oh, right.

112
00:10:11,610 --> 00:10:14,140
He's filthy rich. No joke.

113
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:15,940
It's fake news. Fake news.

114
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:17,530
It's not fake news.

115
00:10:17,530 --> 00:10:20,240
Why do you still live there when you're so rich?

116
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,380
You should move now.

117
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:24,270
Did Old Man secretly save up that much money?

118
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,430
How is that secretly?

119
00:10:25,430 --> 00:10:27,220
And I'm not that rich.

120
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:29,050
But why is Senior Sang Ki called Old Man?

121
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:32,350
- He acts like one, don't you think?
- Come on!

122
00:10:32,350 --> 00:10:34,590
Not at all. He's an absolute fox.

123
00:10:34,590 --> 00:10:36,090
What was your original nickname?

124
00:10:36,090 --> 00:10:38,060
You probably had one in school.

125
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:40,300
I was "Spirit of Spring."

126
00:10:44,110 --> 00:10:45,350
Was that supposed to be funny?

127
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:48,340
It wasn't funny, nor was it touching

128
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:50,150
or thought provoking.

129
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,870
Hey, you pay for all this.

130
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:54,210
You're not funny, but you're rich.

131
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:56,800
- You're crossing the line.
- Hey, aren't you richer, though?

132
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,700
That's my dad's money, not mine.

133
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:01,390
Your dad is rich?

134
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:03,820
My dad may be the CEO of a small, high-potential SME,

135
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:05,360
but he's not that rich.

136
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:07,350
He made some money as Hanguk Group's subcontractor.

137
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:10,440
If not for that, he would've gone under already.

138
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,850
How many times do I have to tell you?

139
00:11:11,850 --> 00:11:13,310
I've never heard that before.

140
00:11:13,310 --> 00:11:17,270
In any case, it's all your money in the end, Mr. Only Child.

141
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:19,810
I'm sick of that "only child" stuff.

142
00:11:19,810 --> 00:11:22,810
Do you want to go up against the 6 million "only child" out there?

143
00:11:22,810 --> 00:11:24,520
And you guys are all doing pretty well.

144
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,660
Who says?

145
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:27,330
You guys all graduated from law school.

146
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:29,760
Gosh, that's a dangerous comment.

147
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:36,300
Not everyone's well-off like you.

148
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:39,580
Others mistake us as such, but you know that's not the case for us.

149
00:11:39,580 --> 00:11:43,880
Why are you getting so serious, Mr. Big Savings Account?

150
00:11:50,380 --> 00:11:52,840
Geez, why did you have to bring up money?

151
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,000
You did, Attorney Jo.

152
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,280
Yeah, I was talking to myself.

153
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,590
This damn mouth of mine.

154
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:59,580
My mouth is the problem.

155
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:08,550
Your symptoms haven't improved.

156
00:12:09,450 --> 00:12:13,640
I couldn't take the meds you prescribed because I got pregnant.

157
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:16,070
Really? Congratulations.

158
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:19,020
Your husband must've been thrilled.

159
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:23,600
I'm not sure yet…

160
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:26,860
I don't know if it's something to celebrate.

161
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:34,280
Then, I'll prescribe something safe for pregnancy.

162
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:03,210
Retail investors are idiots.

163
00:13:03,210 --> 00:13:04,860
As soon as the price goes up a little,

164
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:07,860
they swarm in like rabid dogs.

165
00:13:08,340 --> 00:13:10,500
Are you talking about me?

166
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,020
- You were a retail investor?
- Yes, of course!

167
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:14,820
Oh, shit.

168
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:18,170
That's hilarious.

169
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:19,930
Sorry about that.

170
00:13:19,930 --> 00:13:21,950
- Anyway...
- Yeah?

171
00:13:21,950 --> 00:13:25,460
As soon as trading resumes, we dump all our shares.

172
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:28,470
But these retail investors just gobble them up.

173
00:13:28,470 --> 00:13:30,280
So, we make capital gains,

174
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:33,570
while that stock plummets into penny-stock territory.

175
00:13:33,570 --> 00:13:35,960
Then, we do another capital reduction, rake in capital gains,

176
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:38,430
and repeat this cycle until the company gets delisted.

177
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:39,730
So, that's how I lost my money.

178
00:13:39,730 --> 00:13:43,000
It seems like all my money went to you.

179
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,500
Do you want to partner up when I get out?

180
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:49,040
I'll make you rich.

181
00:13:52,010 --> 00:13:54,250
I appreciate the thought, but I'll pass.

182
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:57,750
If I'm meant to make money, it'll come my way.

183
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:01,540
Otherwise, I'll lose my license.

184
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:09,070
What will you do with your precious attorney license?

185
00:14:09,070 --> 00:14:12,560
Dammit, you're just here as an errand boy to chat with me.

186
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:18,740
I get to run my mouth and get paid for it.

187
00:14:18,740 --> 00:14:20,190
I'd say that's a win.

188
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:21,990
Don't you think?

189
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,500
- You're totally nuts, huh?
- Huh?

190
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,410
This is why I like you, Attorney.

191
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:32,500
Thank you.

192
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,030
Mr. Seong,

193
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:36,740
how long do I have to go on these visitations?

194
00:14:36,740 --> 00:14:40,450
Do you know how much we're being paid for those visitations?

195
00:14:40,450 --> 00:14:44,110
If you can bring in that much business, I'll tell you.

196
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:45,870
Or...

197
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:48,750
if you get your father's company to sign an advisory retainer,

198
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:51,070
I'll take you off the visitation case.

199
00:14:54,220 --> 00:14:58,130
- Never mind.
- The trial won't take long, so just keep doing it.

200
00:14:58,130 --> 00:15:01,160
You don't have to go every day. Maybe every other day.

201
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:03,880
Okay, I understand.

202
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:06,910
Isn't this easier for you anyway?

203
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:10,220
You just go and hang out.

204
00:15:10,220 --> 00:15:13,770
If I were you, I'd say, "Thank you very much" and be on my way.

205
00:16:08,090 --> 00:16:13,500
This isn't theft. It's technically misappropriation of lost property.

206
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:16,310
I honestly don't remember anything.

207
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:18,750
Did you drink a lot that night?

208
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,770
My job-hunting wasn't going well,

209
00:16:20,770 --> 00:16:24,440
so I went out with some friends to blow off steam.

210
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:27,110
I guess I went overboard.

211
00:16:27,110 --> 00:16:30,010
Do you remember going to the convenience store?

212
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,700
I don't remember that, either,

213
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:36,290
but when I get drunk, I usually go there to grab one last beer.

214
00:16:36,290 --> 00:16:38,280
So, I probably went there, but...

215
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:40,880
the police say the CCTV footage shows

216
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:43,830
that I took the watch that was there.

217
00:16:43,830 --> 00:16:46,630
But if you took it, it should be at your house.

218
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,300
But there's nothing.

219
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,750
That's what's driving me crazy.

220
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:52,500
If it were at home, I could at least apologize and say

221
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,790
I mistakenly took it while drunk.

222
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:57,100
But that's not the case.

223
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:03,000
Then, at the police interview, don't accept the charges.

224
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:07,000
Just tell them honestly that you don't remember anything.

225
00:17:08,140 --> 00:17:12,960
But what if they think I'm lying and punish me more harshly?

226
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:15,180
During the police investigation,

227
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:18,660
they may or may not show you the CCTV footage.

228
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:22,000
If you say you don't remember, they'll probably show you video evidence.

229
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,970
It's not too late to admit guilt, then.

230
00:17:26,390 --> 00:17:28,360
I really didn't hit them.

231
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:29,870
In over 10 years of teaching,

232
00:17:29,870 --> 00:17:32,930
I've never used corporal punishment.

233
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:37,940
Are these the students' names?

234
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:41,790
No, they filed the complaint under the parents' names.

235
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:44,080
Then, do you know which kids filed the complaint?

236
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:45,650
Yes, I know who they are.

237
00:17:45,650 --> 00:17:48,070
They were using the gym after school without permission,

238
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:49,350
so I scolded them.

239
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:51,550
A few days later, I got a call from the police,

240
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:54,140
saying I was being sued for child abuse.

241
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:57,900
But are seventh graders even considered children?

242
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:01,950
Yes, anyone under 18 is considered a child.

243
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,290
So, you're saying you only gave them a warning

244
00:18:04,290 --> 00:18:06,320
and didn't physically discipline them. Right?

245
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,710
Yes.

246
00:18:07,710 --> 00:18:09,750
But it says you made them get into the push-up position

247
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:11,320
and hit their bottoms.

248
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:12,470
I never did that.

249
00:18:12,470 --> 00:18:14,350
When the police called me,

250
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:17,070
I wondered if I'd been too harsh with my words.

251
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:18,550
But when I read the complaint,

252
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:21,360
I was shocked by their claims.

253
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:24,690
I only scold students verbally.

254
00:18:24,690 --> 00:18:26,790
Gently.

255
00:18:30,060 --> 00:18:33,250
I see. Could you tell me the students' names?

256
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:53,200
I feel like they'll be on here...

257
00:19:17,410 --> 00:19:20,270
Geez, I told you to knock!

258
00:19:20,270 --> 00:19:22,410
Do you have a Newstagram account?

259
00:19:22,410 --> 00:19:23,310
Huh?

260
00:19:23,310 --> 00:19:25,500
Why don't you create your own account and check?

261
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,380
Why are you making me do it?

262
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:29,720
It's a hassle. I don't know the system, either.

263
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:32,400
And who has the time to read all the terms and conditions?

264
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,870
- Why would you read that?
- That's how you sign up.

265
00:19:34,870 --> 00:19:36,900
Who knows what might be included there?

266
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:39,360
You're nuts.

