00:36:32,470 --> 00:36:34,110
You even went to the school to meet those kids!

532
00:36:34,110 --> 00:36:35,540
I went for work, not for fun.

533
00:36:35,540 --> 00:36:37,120
School? Why would he go to a school?

534
00:36:37,120 --> 00:36:39,480
Well, there were these kids

535
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:42,170
who falsely accused a teacher of corporal punishment.

536
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:44,880
Whoa, scary. So scary.

537
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:48,160
It's too scary to raise kids these days.

538
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:54,170
So, did it get resolved?

539
00:36:54,170 --> 00:36:55,980
Yeah, I think so.

540
00:36:55,980 --> 00:36:57,920
It's a relief.

541
00:36:58,680 --> 00:37:00,640
What are you relieved about?

542
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:04,810
Well, it means my client wasn't a bad person.

543
00:37:06,050 --> 00:37:08,400
Why is that important to you?

544
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:11,160
I'd prefer my client to be a good person.

545
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,590
Who are you?

546
00:37:12,590 --> 00:37:14,890
Who are you? Are you ill?

547
00:37:14,890 --> 00:37:16,460
- He's weird.
- He's always been weird.

548
00:37:16,460 --> 00:37:17,690
He's weirder today.

549
00:37:17,690 --> 00:37:19,540
I think you're right.

550
00:37:19,540 --> 00:37:21,180
I'm so full.

551
00:37:21,180 --> 00:37:22,420
Thanks for dinner.

552
00:37:22,420 --> 00:37:24,520
- Thanks for dinner.
- See you.

553
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:37,500
It's such a relief that my client isn't a bad person.

554
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:40,810
I'd prefer him to be a good person.

555
00:37:41,810 --> 00:37:45,420
I'd prefer my client to be a good person.

556
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:04,200
Gosh, seriously.

557
00:38:05,290 --> 00:38:06,770
Attorney.

558
00:38:06,770 --> 00:38:09,290
Do you want me to tell you something interesting?

559
00:38:09,290 --> 00:38:11,810
- What is it?
- Do you know why

560
00:38:11,810 --> 00:38:14,870
my dad assigned you to me?

561
00:38:14,870 --> 00:38:18,760
Well, to keep you company, I suppose.

562
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:20,310
I'm telling you, you're so funny.

563
00:38:20,310 --> 00:38:22,530
You're so naive.

564
00:38:22,530 --> 00:38:24,680
He assigned you to keep an eye on me.

565
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:27,350
In case I'd rat that old man out.

566
00:38:28,350 --> 00:38:30,440
- Pardon?
- Where do you think I got the money?

567
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,890
It's all that old man's.

568
00:38:31,890 --> 00:38:36,200
But he's such a scaredy-cat.

569
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:39,400
Why would I rat out my dad? I'll be out soon anyway.

570
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,130
I've looked at the case records.

571
00:38:41,130 --> 00:38:44,590
It doesn't look like you'll be out anytime soon.

572
00:38:45,500 --> 00:38:49,100
Do you want to bet? Whether I get out soon or not?

573
00:38:50,380 --> 00:38:52,960
I shouldn't be telling anyone about this.

574
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:56,010
It's a multi-million won tip.

575
00:38:58,910 --> 00:39:01,370
You see, the stock-manipulation cases

576
00:39:01,370 --> 00:39:04,620
are about to whom the unjust gain—

577
00:39:05,660 --> 00:39:07,640
No, never mind.

578
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:09,730
When I get out, do you want to work for me?

579
00:39:09,730 --> 00:39:12,670
I'll tell you then.

580
00:39:12,670 --> 00:39:16,460
I mean, you're already getting paid to hang out with me.

581
00:39:16,460 --> 00:39:18,510
You can stop pretending to be an attorney

582
00:39:18,510 --> 00:39:22,610
and just play with me while working for me.

583
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:24,600
I think that would be fun.

584
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:29,980
Why on earth would I work for you, Jang Su Gil?

585
00:39:31,610 --> 00:39:33,780
What's with that look?

586
00:39:34,630 --> 00:39:38,990
Does glaring at me with prideful eyes make things better?

587
00:39:38,990 --> 00:39:42,950
Why would I assert my pride in front of a lowlife like you?

588
00:39:42,950 --> 00:39:46,330
You're not getting out. Not in 10 or 20 years. Got that, asshole?

589
00:39:46,330 --> 00:39:49,220
You can't even get out of here. What the...

590
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:52,760
Who the hell are you to tell me to work for you?

591
00:39:56,150 --> 00:39:57,970
If I'm a lowlife,

592
00:39:57,970 --> 00:40:01,180
what does that make you, coming here to keep me entertained?

593
00:40:03,450 --> 00:40:07,130
You'll be back here in a few days anyway.

594
00:40:08,180 --> 00:40:10,550
Don't assert your pride.

595
00:40:10,550 --> 00:40:12,900
It'll only eat you up inside.

596
00:40:34,930 --> 00:40:37,260
Thank you, Attorney.

597
00:40:37,260 --> 00:40:40,400
I'll do my best to teach the kids well.

598
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:44,080
- A girl you're flirting with?
- Geez, you scared me.

599
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:46,840
- Why smile while reading a text?
- You're wrong.

600
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:48,700
Let's go.

601
00:40:48,700 --> 00:40:51,550
- Is it really a girl you're flirting with?
- No, no. Let's go.

602
00:40:51,550 --> 00:40:52,800
Enjoy your meal.

603
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:53,960
- Enjoy your meal.
- Okay.

604
00:40:53,960 --> 00:40:55,030
What are you having?

605
00:40:55,030 --> 00:40:56,520
We'll have Chinese spicy soup.

606
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:58,740
Chinese spicy soup sounds good.

607
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:02,320
What are we having?

608
00:41:03,030 --> 00:41:05,160
I'm not sure.

609
00:41:10,510 --> 00:41:12,140
Hey, are you heading out to eat?

610
00:41:12,140 --> 00:41:13,380
Of course.

611
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:14,980
Aren't we eating together?

612
00:41:14,980 --> 00:41:17,940
I think I'll have to eat separately today.

613
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:20,470
You didn't say that in the group chat.

614
00:41:20,470 --> 00:41:23,260
Why argue about it? She must have something to do.

615
00:41:23,260 --> 00:41:25,450
- I mean...
- An Ju Hyeong.

616
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:28,240
I have a life, too.

617
00:41:35,210 --> 00:41:37,400
- I'll get going.
- Okay, see you later.

618
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:40,300
- Make sure to eat.
- Okay!

619
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,960
What is it?

620
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:50,250
As I thought...

621
00:41:57,780 --> 00:41:59,420
What?

622
00:41:59,420 --> 00:42:01,660
Naengmyeon* sounds good.
(Cold noodles with vinegar*, also used to mean jealousy)

623
00:42:01,660 --> 00:42:03,200
- Okay, naengmyeon.
- Today's a naengmyeon day.

624
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:05,220
Yeah, naengmyeon.

625
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:11,030
Enjoy your meal.

626
00:42:11,030 --> 00:42:12,650
- Thank you.
- Sure thing.

627
00:42:12,650 --> 00:42:15,380
- Are you leaving?
- Yes.

628
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,420
Yes, thank you. Come again.

629
00:42:19,420 --> 00:42:21,510
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

630
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:28,620
Sir, the black bean noodles are really good.

631
00:42:28,620 --> 00:42:31,360
Our black soybean paste sauce isn't just any black soybean paste.

632
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:33,550
But I still can't show you the CCTV footage.

633
00:42:33,550 --> 00:42:36,700
I'll only check the part with my client. That'll be enough.

634
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:41,000
I've explained enough already. Bring the police with you.

635
00:42:48,520 --> 00:42:50,960
Gosh, this is tasty.

636
00:42:55,130 --> 00:42:57,170
Thank you.

637
00:42:57,170 --> 00:43:00,340
- Hey, pull that in a bit.
- Gosh, seriously.

638
00:43:01,580 --> 00:43:04,180
Nice. That's good.

639
00:43:06,340 --> 00:43:08,350
But who eats cold noodles in the middle of winter?

640
00:43:08,350 --> 00:43:10,160
It's originally a cold region dish.

641
00:43:10,160 --> 00:43:12,550
I bet people there don't eat cold noodles in the winter.

642
00:43:12,550 --> 00:43:15,680
You don't even drink iced Americanos when it's cold, but you'll eat this?

643
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:18,280
Mun Jeong strongly wanted to eat it.

644
00:43:18,280 --> 00:43:21,240
She always strongly wants to eat.

645
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,830
Then, why didn't you order beef short rib soup?

646
00:43:22,830 --> 00:43:24,530
Why do you always complain every time we eat?

647
00:43:24,530 --> 00:43:26,700
How can I get beef short rib soup when everyone is having cold noodles?

648
00:43:26,700 --> 00:43:28,680
That's true.

649
00:43:29,850 --> 00:43:31,470
One order of cold noodles with broth for this table.

650
00:43:31,470 --> 00:43:33,270
Yes, yes.

651
00:43:34,190 --> 00:43:35,210
Hello?

652
00:43:35,210 --> 00:43:36,450
Yeah, Hyung.

653
00:43:36,450 --> 00:43:39,760
Yeah, I'm part of Hyungmin Law Group.

654
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:41,620
Kang Hui Ji?

655
00:43:42,490 --> 00:43:45,450
Yeah, I know Hui Ji well. Why?

656
00:43:55,520 --> 00:43:58,820
Hey, I called you to stop this attorney from coming here.

657
00:43:58,820 --> 00:44:00,830
- But you come with her?
- What's wrong?

658
00:44:00,830 --> 00:44:02,440
It's nice to see you again.

659
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:03,950
You two must be really close.

660
00:44:03,950 --> 00:44:06,740
- I'm a regular here.
- He always brings girls here to impress them.

661
00:44:06,740 --> 00:44:07,970
That's how he became a regular.

662
00:44:07,970 --> 00:44:10,800
Hyung! Why would you say that? She'll misunderstand!

663
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:13,260
Huh? Why are you getting flustered? Trying to impress her?

664
00:44:13,260 --> 00:44:16,670
What are you saying? This guy's weird.

665
00:44:16,670 --> 00:44:19,640
But how do you impress girls here?

666
00:44:19,640 --> 00:44:22,100
Well, you see...

667
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:24,850
- That's a trade secret.
- What a load of crap.

668
00:44:24,850 --> 00:44:26,530
I can't let you see it.

669
00:44:26,530 --> 00:44:29,590
But since you came with Chang Won, enjoy your meal.

670
00:44:29,590 --> 00:44:31,890
I'll give you cream shrimp on the house.

671
00:44:31,890 --> 00:44:34,790
Thank you. I'll come often.

672
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:37,520
- Hello.
- Hello.

673
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:40,060
- See you later.
- See you.

674
00:44:51,420 --> 00:44:54,150
Goodness, sorry for the wait.

675
00:44:55,020 --> 00:44:57,430
- Please enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

676
00:44:57,430 --> 00:44:58,800
This is good.

677
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:01,500
They're really making me uncomfortable.

678
00:45:10,410 --> 00:45:11,410
It's burned.

679
00:45:11,410 --> 00:45:13,480
If you burn it like this, I can't post a picture.

680
00:45:13,480 --> 00:45:14,550
- I mean—
- Leave that one out.

681
00:45:14,550 --> 00:45:16,510
It got burned because I was waiting for you.

682
00:45:16,510 --> 00:45:17,950
This one doesn't look tasty, either.

683
00:45:17,950 --> 00:45:20,020
- Put a new one on for me. Just one.
- Okay, okay.

684
00:45:20,020 --> 00:45:21,940
- A new one. Nice.
- It's frozen.

685
00:45:21,940 --> 00:45:23,550
The lighting's good. Got it.

686
00:45:23,550 --> 00:45:25,780
- You're good now?
- Okay, okay.

687
00:45:31,460 --> 00:45:32,730
Oops, my bad.

688
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:34,730
- Is this revenge?
- I'm eating the burned ones for you.

689
00:45:34,730 --> 00:45:36,510
All right.

690
00:45:43,020 --> 00:45:44,890
Here's your fried rice.

691
00:45:47,170 --> 00:45:49,850
All right, enjoy your meal.

692
00:45:54,590 --> 00:45:56,120
Don't smile.

693
00:45:56,120 --> 00:45:58,250
Come on.

694
00:46:13,100 --> 00:46:15,860
I think it'd work with one more visit.

695
00:46:15,860 --> 00:46:19,210
Right? With one more visit, we might throw up.

696
00:46:19,210 --> 00:46:21,150
Gosh, this damn convenience store table.

697
00:46:21,150 --> 00:46:24,280
Why did he have to leave it here?

698
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:27,750
Still, you're such a hard worker.

699
00:46:28,550 --> 00:46:30,260
Sorry for dragging you into this.

700
00:46:30,260 --> 00:46:31,700
Oh, no.

701
00:46:31,700 --> 00:46:35,110
Following you makes me feel like I'm working hard,

702
00:46:35,110 --> 00:46:37,120
so it's fun. I like it.

703
00:46:37,120 --> 00:46:38,410
Really?

704
00:46:38,410 --> 00:46:40,750
Then, does this seem like interesting work?

705
00:46:40,750 --> 00:46:43,940
You said you wanted to do something exciting and worthwhile.

706
00:46:43,940 --> 00:46:48,570
Well, it seems way better than my work.

707
00:46:49,770 --> 00:46:53,530
I guess being an attorney doesn't suit me.

708
00:46:53,530 --> 00:46:56,220
Why not? You're the most energetic guy at our firm.

709
00:46:56,220 --> 00:47:00,030
I'm only enjoying myself because you guys are there.

710
00:47:00,030 --> 00:47:03,090
The job itself... I'm not sure about it.

711
00:47:03,090 --> 00:47:05,330
Still, if you don't want to be an attorney,

712
00:47:05,330 --> 00:47:07,130
you could always inherit your dad's business.

713
00:47:07,130 --> 00:47:08,390
Gosh, seriously.

714
00:47:08,390 --> 00:47:09,820
That's my dad's company, not mine.

715
00:47:09,820 --> 00:47:11,950
How many times do I have to tell you?

716
00:47:11,950 --> 00:47:14,870
What about you? You said your dad also runs a business.

717
00:47:14,870 --> 00:47:16,880
Yeah.

718
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:18,770
Just a moment.

719
00:47:19,700 --> 00:47:21,670
Yeah, Dad.

720
00:47:21,670 --> 00:47:25,220
No, I didn't forget. We talked about it last time.

721
00:47:25,910 --> 00:47:28,850
Oh, next Friday?

722
00:47:28,850 --> 00:47:30,440
Got it.

723
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:32,440
Okay.

724
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:36,280
What is it? Something happening next Friday?

725
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:38,900
Yeah. My parents' memorial service.

726
00:47:39,540 --> 00:47:41,230
What?

727
00:47:41,230 --> 00:47:43,380
What? What's the matter?

728
00:47:44,210 --> 00:47:48,730
I mean, just now on the phone,

729
00:47:48,730 --> 00:47:50,260
didn't you call him "D-Dad"?

730
00:47:50,260 --> 00:47:52,960
Yeah, I was talking to my dad.

731
00:47:53,900 --> 00:47:57,010
Then, it's your mom's memorial?

732
00:47:57,010 --> 00:47:59,090
No, for both of my parents.

733
00:47:59,090 --> 00:48:00,650
What?

734
00:48:02,060 --> 00:48:04,900
My parents passed away when I was seven.

735
00:48:04,900 --> 00:48:07,330
My aunt and uncle raised me.

736
00:48:07,330 --> 00:48:10,180
So, my uncle is now my dad.

737
00:48:13,200 --> 00:48:15,000
I see.

738
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:18,100
Then...

739
00:48:18,100 --> 00:48:23,640
your dad, who runs a business, is the uncle you were just talking to...

740
00:48:23,640 --> 00:48:26,380
No, no, I mean, he's your dad.

741
00:48:26,380 --> 00:48:28,980
Wait, no. You said your dad passed away,

742
00:48:28,980 --> 00:48:31,410
so...

743
00:48:32,400 --> 00:48:35,300
It's really difficult, right? You don't have to say anything.

744
00:48:35,300 --> 00:48:36,960
No, I feel like...

745
00:48:36,960 --> 00:48:40,810
I should still s-say something.

746
00:48:40,810 --> 00:48:43,350
No, no, just be quiet.

747
00:48:43,350 --> 00:48:45,580
- Can I?
- Yeah, just stay still.

748
00:48:45,580 --> 00:48:47,630
I'm fine.

749
00:48:48,190 --> 00:48:49,980
Thanks.

750
00:49:23,430 --> 00:49:26,500
We've narrowed down to five scholarship recipients this year.

751
00:49:26,500 --> 00:49:29,730
Four 12th graders and one exam retaker.

752
00:49:30,510 --> 00:49:34,410
This student's family income fluctuates every year.

753
00:49:34,410 --> 00:49:38,000
Let's do another background check to make sure

754
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:41,500
they didn't under-report before making a final decision.

755
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:42,790
Yes, understood.

756
00:49:42,790 --> 00:49:45,930
Executive Director, Lee Dong Su, one of the first-year recipients...

757
00:49:45,930 --> 00:49:47,700
Him again?

758
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,290
What about the victim?

759
00:49:52,290 --> 00:49:53,790
They haven't hired an attorney yet, right?

760
00:49:53,790 --> 00:49:57,110
Yes, it seems they are representing themselves.

761
00:49:58,480 --> 00:50:02,330
Should we pay the victim for their legal fees again?

762
00:50:02,330 --> 00:50:04,370
No.

763
00:50:04,370 --> 00:50:07,750
This time, let's not just pay for their attorney fees.

764
00:50:07,750 --> 00:50:10,080
Let's bring them here.

765
00:50:11,200 --> 00:50:14,150
This is the Hyungmin Law Group, after all.

766
00:50:14,150 --> 00:50:16,960
We'll have the attorneys here represent them.

767
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:20,920
I've always wanted to do that once I opened my own firm.

768
00:50:20,920 --> 00:50:22,950
Okay, understood.

769
00:50:28,750 --> 00:50:30,890
- Gosh, it's cold.
- Welcome—

770
00:50:31,860 --> 00:50:33,920
Gosh, seriously.

771
00:50:33,920 --> 00:50:36,400
I'm so sick and tired of this.

772
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:42,620
Are you sure it's okay to show it to you?

773
00:50:42,620 --> 00:50:45,870
That's right! It's fine as long as you don't show me other people.

774
00:50:45,870 --> 00:50:47,400
Have that guy come, too.

775
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:50,060
- He lives around here, right?
- Yes!

776
00:50:50,060 --> 00:50:52,030
You better take responsibility if I get in trouble for this.

777
00:50:52,030 --> 00:50:54,130
Come on, Hyung. We're attorneys.

778
00:50:54,130 --> 00:50:56,070
- I have a criminal record.
- I'll defend you.

779
00:50:56,070 --> 00:50:57,530
Deal.

780
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:57,530
Why'd you do that?

781
00:52:20,060 --> 00:52:22,400
I can't even get a job,

782
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:27,450
and I stole someone's stuff after getting drunk.

783
00:52:31,740 --> 00:52:35,130
Wow, I'm such a scumbag.

784
00:52:55,320 --> 00:52:58,290
What do I do now, Attorney?

785
00:52:58,290 --> 00:53:00,580
Act like you don't know anything.

786
00:53:01,960 --> 00:53:05,220
That's how I should advise you as an attorney.

787
00:53:05,220 --> 00:53:08,930
It won't be easy to prove you did it with only the police's CCTV footage.

788
00:53:08,930 --> 00:53:10,720
But...

789
00:53:11,730 --> 00:53:15,310
if I were your older sister,

790
00:53:15,310 --> 00:53:19,630
